| SRH | IPv6 header carrying segments |
| Service Chaining | Forcing traffic through services |

---

## âš¡ In Simple Terms

Normal routing:
Routers decide the path.

SRv6 routing:
The packet itself decides the path.

No tunnels.  
No MPLS.  
No magic boxes.

Just IPv6 packets carrying instructions.

This is clean, brutal, and scalable.

